<P>ZELAVTO. THE FOVN|taine of <HI>Fame.</HI> Erected in an Orcharde of Amorous Aduentures. Containing A Delicate <HI>Disputation,</HI> gallantly discoursed betweene two noble Gentlemen of <HI>Italye.</HI> Giuen for a freendly entertainment to <HI>Euphues,</HI> at his late ariuall into England. By <HI>A. M.</HI> Seruaunt to the Right Ho|nourable the Earle of Oxenford.</P>
<P>Honos alit Artes.</P>
<P>&para; Imprinted at London by <HI>Iohn</HI> Charlevvood. 1580.</P>
</DIV1>
