<HEAD>The Author.</HEAD>
<P>THus hath <HI>Zelauto</HI> and <HI>Astraepho</HI> passed one day in talke together, and now are gone to prouide such necessaries as are n&eacute;edefull to suffice theyr hungrie stomackes: howe they spent the next day: the matter ensuing shall make manifest. Thus y&eacute;elding my selfe (gentle Reader) vnto thy courteous construction, and not to a rashe Reporters reprehen|sion: I wishe my woorkes might procure th&eacute;e as much pleasure, as my good wyll is to woorke thy welfare. <HI>Vale.</HI></P>
<Q>Honos alit Artes.</Q>
